    • Method Detail

      • findOperationsConsumingAll

        Map<URI,MatchResult> findOperationsConsumingAll(Set<URI> inputTypes)
        Discover registered operations that consume all the types of input provided. That is, all those that have as input the types provided. All the input types should be matched to different inputs.
        Parameters:
        inputTypes - the types of input to be consumed
        Returns:
        a Set containing all the matching operations. If there are no solutions, the Set should be empty, not null.

      • findOperationsConsumingSome

        Map<URI,MatchResult> findOperationsConsumingSome(Set<URI> inputTypes)
        Discover registered operations that consume some (i.e., at least one) of the types of input provided. That is, all those that have as input the types provided.
        Parameters:
        inputTypes - the types of input to be consumed
        Returns:
        a Set containing all the matching operations. If there are no solutions, the Set should be empty, not null.

      • findOperationsProducingAll

        Map<URI,MatchResult> findOperationsProducingAll(Set<URI> outputTypes)
        Discover registered operations that produce all of the types of output provided. That is, all those that can be matched to the output types provided. Note, each output should be matched to a different type.
        Parameters:
        outputTypes - the types of output to be produced
        Returns:
        a Set containing all the matching operations. If there are no solutions, the Set should be empty, not null.

      • findOperationsProducingSome

        Map<URI,MatchResult> findOperationsProducingSome(Set<URI> outputTypes)
        Discover registered operations that produce some (i.e., at least one) of the types of output provided. That is, all those for which at least one output can be matched to the output types provided.
        Parameters:
        outputTypes - the types of output to be produced
        Returns:
        a Set containing all the matching operations. If there are no solutions, the Set should be empty, not null.

      • findOperationsClassifiedByAll

        Map<URI,MatchResult> findOperationsClassifiedByAll(Set<URI> modelReferences)
        Discover the operations that are classified by all the types given. That is, all those that have some level of matching with respect to all operations provided in the model references.
        Parameters:
        modelReferences - the classifications to match against
        Returns:
        a Set containing all the matching operations. If there are no solutions, the Set should be empty, not null.

      • findOperationsClassifiedBySome

        Map<URI,MatchResult> findOperationsClassifiedBySome(Set<URI> modelReferences)
        Discover the operations that are classified by some (i.e., at least one) of the types given. That is, all those that have some level of matching with respect to at least one entity provided in the model references.
        Parameters:
        modelReferences - the classifications to match against
        Returns:
        a Set containing all the matching operations. If there are no solutions, the Set should be empty, not null.

      • findOperationsInvocableWith

        Map<URI,MatchResult> findOperationsInvocableWith(Set<URI> inputTypes)
        Discover registered operations that can be invoked based on the types of input provided. That is, all those that do not have any mandatory input that cannot be fulfilled with the provided ones.
        Parameters:
        inputTypes - the types of inputs provided
        Returns:
        a Set containing all the invocable operations. If there are no solutions, the Set should be empty, not null.
